                  <msItem>
                     <p> FILBY. <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> de <surname>Cressy</surname>
                        </persName>, with the assent of
               <persName>
                           <forename>Isabella</forename> de <surname>Cressy</surname>
                        </persName> 
                        <pb n="240"/> his mother,
                  grants to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> 
                              <surname>Sparham</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> and
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Ranulfia</forename> his wife</persName>, the whole of his land of his manor of 
                  <placeName type="manor" key="place_104057">Filby</placeName>, with appurtenances, paying annually to the 
                  <orgName role="abbot" key="org_104001">abbot of St. Bennet of Hulme</orgName> 10s. 8d., and
                  scutage to the King so much as pertains to the third part of one knight's fee. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1250" notAfter="1260" precision="low">c. 1250-60</origDate>.) (Hugh Cressy died in 1262.)
                  . </p>
                  </msItem>
